@startuml
[*] as Initial State
state "User Login" as A
state "Destination Selection" as B
state "Journey Details Displayed" as C
state "Driving Mode Activated" as D
state "Other Options Selected" as E
state "Place to Eat Selected" as F
state "Menu Viewed" as G
state "Order Placed" as H
state "Accident Occurred" as I
state "Notification Sent" as J
state "Feedback Provided" as K

A --> B : User Login and Destination Selection
B --> C : Journey Details Displayed upon Destination Selection
C -->|D/E|> D/E : Activate Driving Mode or Choose Other Options
D --> F : Select Place to Eat in Driving Mode
E --> G : View Menu in Other Options
F --> H : Order Placed after Viewing Menu
G --> H : Order Placed after Viewing Menu
H --> I : Accident Occurred during Journey
I --> J : Notification Sent in Case of an Accident
J --> K : Feedback Provided upon Completion of Journey

[*] --> A : Initial State (User Login)
C --> [*] : Final State (Feedback Provided)

@enduml
